---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About">
  <section class="border-b border-surface-3">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-2">About HN HRCB</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400">Hacker News stories scored against the Universal Declaration of Human Rights.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 space-y-10">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">What is this?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        HN HRCB is a mirror of Hacker News that evaluates every story's linked content against the
        30 articles and preamble of the UN Universal Declaration of Human Rights. Each evaluation
        produces a Human Rights Compatibility Bias (HRCB) score showing how the content's editorial
        and structural signals align with fundamental human rights provisions.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        A cron worker fetches top HN stories every 10 minutes, retrieves each linked URL's content,
        and uses Claude Haiku to evaluate it against the UDHR methodology (v3.4). Results are stored
        and displayed alongside the standard HN story metadata.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Core Construct: HRCB</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        <strong class="text-white">Human Rights Compatibility Bias (HRCB)</strong> measures the directional lean
        of web content relative to the provisions of the UN Universal Declaration of Human Rights.
        A positive score indicates content that aligns with UDHR provisions; a negative score indicates
        content that conflicts with them.
      </p>
      <div class="card p-4 score-font text-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 justify-center">
          <span class="text-red-400">-1.0</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500">&larr;</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400">Strong negative</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500">|</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400">Neutral</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500">|</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400">Strong positive</span>
          <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
          <span class="text-green-400">+1.0</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Signal Channels -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Signal Channels</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="card p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 mb-2">Editorial (E)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            What the content <strong class="text-gray-300">says</strong>. Analyzes the text, arguments,
            framing, and sourcing of the content itself.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-400 mb-2">Structural (S)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            What the site <strong class="text-gray-300">does</strong>. Examines privacy practices,
            accessibility, tracking, access models, and platform policies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">
        Channels are weighted by content type (e.g., editorial content: E=0.6, S=0.4).
        The combined score is: <span class="score-font">(w_E &times; E) + (w_S &times; S)</span>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ND vs 0.0 -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">ND vs 0.0</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="card p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 mb-2">ND (No Data)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            No relevant content for this UDHR article. The topic is simply absent. Not scored, not averaged.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-300 mb-2">0.0 (Neutral)</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
            Relevant content exists but has balanced positive and negative signals, netting to zero.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Domain Context Profile -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Domain Context Profile (DCP)</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Eight domain-level elements provide context modifiers that adjust article scores based on
        the website's overall practices:
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-2">
        {['Privacy', 'ToS', 'Accessibility', 'Mission', 'Editorial Code', 'Ownership', 'Access Model', 'Ad/Tracking'].map((el) => (
          <div class="card p-3 text-center">
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">{el}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">
        Modifiers range from -0.20 to +0.30 (capped) and apply only to specified articles.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Evidence Strength -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Evidence Strength</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-green-500/20 text-green-400 w-8 justify-center">H</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">High — direct, explicit content with strong sourcing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-yellow-500/20 text-yellow-400 w-8 justify-center">M</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Medium — clear signal but may be secondary or partially sourced</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-gray-500/20 text-gray-400 w-8 justify-center">L</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Low — tangential, indirect, or weakly sourced</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Directionality -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Directionality Markers</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-indigo-500/20 text-indigo-400 w-8 justify-center">A</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Advocacy — explicitly argues for or against a right</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-cyan-500/20 text-cyan-400 w-8 justify-center">P</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Practice — site infrastructure reflects a rights stance</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-violet-500/20 text-violet-400 w-8 justify-center">F</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Framing — presents issues in a rights-aligned or rights-opposed frame</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="badge bg-orange-500/20 text-orange-400 w-8 justify-center">C</span>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">Content — factual content relevant to human rights topics</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How Evaluations Work -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">How Evaluations Work</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p>Each evaluation follows a structured process:</p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-400">
          <li>A URL from HN's top stories is fetched as the unit of analysis</li>
          <li>The page's content type is classified (Editorial, Commentary, HR, etc.)</li>
          <li>Channel weights are assigned based on content type</li>
          <li>A Domain Context Profile (DCP) is constructed from 8 domain-level elements</li>
          <li>Each of 31 UDHR provisions is scored for editorial and structural signals</li>
          <li>Context modifiers from the DCP are applied to relevant articles</li>
          <li>Aggregate statistics are computed (weighted mean, evidence profile, etc.)</li>
          <li>A final classification is assigned (Strong positive to Strong negative)</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Version history -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Version History</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        {[
          { v: 'v1', desc: 'External-source methodology, domain-level evaluation' },
          { v: 'v2', desc: 'On-domain-only, ND vs 0.0 distinction, evidence strength, off-domain toggle' },
          { v: 'v3', desc: 'URL-level HRCB with E/S channels, content types, rubrics, calibration' },
          { v: 'v3.3', desc: 'Consolidation + roadmap' },
          { v: 'v3.4', desc: 'Current — Batch protocol, adversarial robustness, JSON/CSV machine-readable output' },
        ].map(({ v, desc }) => (
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class={`badge shrink-0 ${v === 'v3.4' ? 'bg-indigo-500/20 text-indigo-400' : 'bg-surface-3 text-gray-400'}`}>
              {v}
            </span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-400">{desc}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Technical Details -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Technical Details</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This site is built with Astro and deployed on Cloudflare Pages with D1 (SQLite) for storage.
        A cron-triggered Cloudflare Worker fetches HN top stories and evaluates them via the Anthropic
        API (Claude Haiku). All visualizations are server-rendered SVG with zero client-side JavaScript.
      </p>
      <div class="card p-4 score-font text-sm text-gray-400">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2">
          <span>Schema version:</span><span class="text-gray-300">3.4</span>
          <span>Methodology:</span><span class="text-gray-300">v3.4</span>
          <span>Evaluator:</span><span class="text-gray-300">claude-haiku-4-5-20251001</span>
          <span>Framework:</span><span class="text-gray-300">Astro + Cloudflare Pages</span>
          <span>Database:</span><span class="text-gray-300">Cloudflare D1 (SQLite)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">The Universal Declaration of Human Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Adopted by the United Nations General Assembly on 10 December 1948 (Resolution 217 A),
        the UDHR is a milestone document in the history of human rights. It sets out, for the
        first time, fundamental human rights to be universally protected. It has been translated
        into over 500 languages.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        The Declaration consists of a Preamble and 30 Articles covering civil, political,
        economic, social, and cultural rights. These range from the right to life and liberty
        (Article 3) to freedom of expression (Article 19) to the right to education (Article 26).
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
